SAVF Cecilia van Wyk Kleuterskool was verlede week oorstelp van vreugde toe Laevelder hulle met ‘n hele sak vol burgers verras het. Altesaam 28 van juffrou Drianie se klas het elk ‘n kaasburger en vrugtesappie van McDonald’s ontvang. Dit is alles te danke aan hoe gehoorsaam, hardwerkend, slim en lewenslustig die gr. RR maatjies was, en natuurlik die held van die dag, Naldo Breytenbach, wie se ma, Charissa, aan Laevelder geskryf het. ALSO READ: Another Burger Bust takes place   One of Laerskool Nelspruit’s grade three classes were the lucky recipients of last Friday’s McDonald’s Nelspruit burger bust. Teacher Suritha van Heerden, was nominated by a parent because of her dedication and willingness to go the extra mile. Van Heerden was pleasantly surprised and the class echoed her excitement with a huge thumbs up for the treat. The youngsters’ excitement matched their teacher’s surprise at the welcome snack. Their admiration of Van Heerden showed in the way a number of the pupils lined up and requested to have their picture taken with her. ALSO READ: McDonald’s spoils more kids with burgers and love The weekly McDonald’s Nelspruit and Lowvelder burger bust is fast becoming an institution in the Lowveld.   If you think your class deserves to be surprised, send Julia Burger your motivation to marketing@lowvelder.co.za. 